50|$|The {{church was}} founded by Dutch missionaries in 1863. The missionaries took a very <b>antithetic</b> <b>attitude</b> toward Islam and the Sundanese culture. The {{progress}} was very slow. Meanwhile, a Dutch layman collected some converts using less orthodox methods with the forms of the Javanese magical learning. In 1885 these two streams united and in 1934, when it had 4,000 members, a synod was formed. In 1942 several hardships occurred and lasted to the fifties because of the Islamic revolts. The church survived, and consolidated. It runs several schools and hospitals.|$|E

